Attached is the revised spreadsheet that includes the CardConnect rates, as well as the

Based on the numbers, if we keep our pricing the same as we currently have it with
First Data, our revenue on the NAPA business would be cut approximately in half
under CardConnect.

With the reduction in interchange that we will be subjected to with
CardConnect, we will need to increase the price to the NAPA stores considerably if we
don't want to lose revenue. With that said, there is only so much we can increase
pricing before we lose a competitive advantage against other solutions in the
marketplace so, as it stands now, it will be challenging to ever get back to our current
revenue level.

CardConnect has offered to pay us $100 per store once they reach 3,000 stores.*
However, we are still working through the agreement terms with them so l haven't
included that potential income in these numbers. Once the agreement is completed,
we can circulate it for review/signature. *There is no guarantee they will reach 3,000
stores.

stores, but I don't think it will be a good fit for them right now, especially since we
will soon be losing the ability to board their stores on First Data. I would be
lying if I said I wasn't a little bummed out. I really wanted it off my plate.
